The paper focuses on deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that has made significant progress in continuous control (cs.RO) and autonomous driving (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a new environment (Continual Ant Maze) and a new metric (Normalized Shorten Distance), which are related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a framework that involves unsupervised learning (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
